<item>
            <title>[LU-5442] unconditionally include libcfs.h in lustre_idl.h</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5442</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lustre_idl.h only includes libcfs.h if LPU64 is not defined:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;#&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; !defined(LPU64)
#include &amp;lt;libcfs/libcfs.h&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; LPUX64, etc */&lt;/span&gt;
#endif
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since the landing of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5327&quot; title=&quot;powerpc64 defines __u64 differently for kernel- and user-space&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5327&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5327&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: add libcfs/types.h it is possible to get definitions for LPU64 without including libcfs.h. (Technically it was always possible, but now it&apos;s much easier.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The outer include guard was added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-113&quot; title=&quot;Dependency issues with RHEL installation - lustre-ldiskfs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-113&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-113&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: make lustre_&lt;/p&gt;
{idl,user}
&lt;p&gt;.h nice to userspace. Since we no longer package lustre_idl.h we should remove this guard.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
